	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>THE SHADOW FALLS: TWILIGHT CH 11 RESOLUTION(COMPLETE! PT1. AND PT .2)</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage Express 2.0">
<title>Untitled Normal Page</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

<p>---------------------<br>
Chapter 11 Resolution<br>
--------------------- </p>

<p>&quot;......&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;For 50th time Reyas I'm sorry!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Tell that to the large bump on the top of my head!&quot;
</p>

<p>&quot;I sowy large bump on Reyas's head.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;O haha.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Hehe. I'm sorry Rey-Rey. I didn't know mortal girls were
so jealous.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;HMPH!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Ok. Now I am completely confused Reyas. What is going on
here?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;It's simple Tenrou, Traica here has a twisted sense of
humor and enjoys seeing me in<br>
awkward situations.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;So she is...&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;My sister.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Oh...So you never...&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;HEY! HEY!!&quot; Traica released Reyas from her bear hug
and walked over to Tenrou and<br>
with hands on her hips, gave him an agitated stare. &quot;For
such a cutie pie, you have a dirty<br>
mind.&quot; </p>

<p>Tenrou began to turn a light red.
&quot;I..uh..um..well....&quot; Traica leaned up against Tenrou<br>
placing her head on his chest. </p>

<p>&quot;I like him. hehe. You have good taste in friends
Rey-Rey&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I try. And stop calling me Rey-Rey! You know I hate that
name!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Well what else am I going to call my little brother? OO!
I know shrimp! OH-OH! Even<br>
better!! Peewee!!! &quot; </p>

<p>Reyas gave a Triaca an aggravated scowl, she feigned fear and
hid behind Tenrou. </p>

<p>&quot;Someone save me from the big monster!!!!&quot; </p>

<p>Tenrou stood adamant, completely befuddled while Triaca
playfully hid away from Reyas. </p>

<p>&quot;You remember that monster crack the next time you want a
massage.&quot; </p>

<p>Traica stopped immediately and looked pained. &quot;Ah! Don't
say that! That's mean.<br>
Especially after a girl has been asleep for several
millennia.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Well too bad&quot; Reyas said flatly while sticking his
tongue at her. </p>

<p>&quot;Meanie&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Yep...speaking of things don't you think you should put
something on?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I thought I noticed a draft.&quot; She said as a very
skimpy outfit formed on her. </p>

<p>&quot;That's it?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Yep!&quot; </p>

<p>Tenrou stared at Traica in a mix of absolute confusion and
desire. </p>

<p>&quot;Are you...sure ..is.... Trakanon?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I ought to know my own sister Ten-&quot; &quot;And my
name is Traica N'on! I hate that stupid<br>
mispronociaton&quot; She barked at Tenrou, cutting Reyas off </p>

<p>&quot;So you are really the feared Traka- I mean Traica N'on.
The poison demon that killed<br>
most of the iksar?&quot; </p>

<p>It was Traica's turn to change too a shade of red as she
mumbled a reply while staring at<br>
the ground. </p>

<p>&quot;Girl has one too many tithes, gets a little gas and
she's marked as a demon for the rest of<br>
her existence...its just not fair...&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;O......k...&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;BUT! That&#146;s all in the past! And now I am awake and
ready to see the world!'&quot; She<br>
cheered &quot;AND your coming with me cutie!&quot; Putting Tenrou
in a vise-like hug. </p>

<p>&quot;My ribs!!!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I think I'll leave you two alone. I need to go find
Leylia.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;NO wait! Come ba- Can't...... breath!..help!&quot;<br>
------------------------------ </p>

<p><br>
&quot;Leylia! Come on! Please! I am telling you the truth! Traica
is my sister!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;That's even worse!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Argh! Not like that!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Hmph!! You would say anything. Typical heartless
chauvinist pig&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;That's cruel and unfair....I am a dragon not a
pig.&quot; </p>

<p>Leylia smiled slightly, turning to face Reyas. </p>

<p>&quot;So there really isn't anything between you two?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Nothing absolutely nothing. Traica is a joker, she loves
to tease all my girlfriends like<br>
that......&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;WHY YOU!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Leylia! Wait!!! Come on! I was kidding! Ah man...here I
go again...&quot;<br>
----------------------------------- </p>

<p>On the other end of the canyon, Tenrou takes a forced stroll
along the river, Traica still<br>
holding him in a tight hug, snuggled up against him. </p>

<p>&quot;Wow. Everything has gotten so pretty since I got put to
sleep.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;What was it like back then?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Well it was pretty back then, but nothing like this..of
course I never did get a chance to<br>
admire the scenery much back then. Before Veeshan kicked me and
Reyas out of the<br>
council, the iksar, Sarnak, Froglok and the Burnyai Legions all
used to give me tithes and<br>
praise at my temple. It was great but with all the praise, food
and miracles I had to<br>
perform, I didn&#146;t get a chance to look around much&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;That&#146;s terrible, what about after she kicked you
out?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Well I got lucky sort of.. After she kicked us out I
simply resumed what I hand been<br>
before. Getting tithes and performing miracles!..that was
until...those bean pastas always<br>
tasted so good...sigh..Well any way after the accident, I felt so
bad that I tried to hid<br>
myself away, but they found me and tried to kill me. I'm not the
demon they thought I<br>
was, I never have been and never will be. So I scared them a
little, pulled a few more<br>
miracles and got them to try putting me to sleep. Unfortunately,
I underestimated the<br>
Froglok shamans....I had only meant to sleep a century or two,
not several millennia. They<br>
just had to read the scroll, but Noooooooooooo! They just had to
experiment! Lucky I<br>
didn't wake up with spots or something.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Say, what are those red things back of your neck?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;WHAT!?!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Gotcha-oof! Hey no hitting!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Serves you right.&quot;<br>
----------------------------- </p>

<p>&quot;I'm sorry I beat on you, I guess I don't take teasing to
well.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;So I am finding out.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;How is your head? I hit you pretty hard.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Aside from the large bump on top of my head, I am
fine.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Well it doesn't seem to big now.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Thank goodness.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Unlike other things. Is that just a dagger in your
pocket or are you really happy to see<br>
me?&quot;<br>
-------------------------------- </p>

<p><br>
As they stand upon a cliff over looking the raging river, below
which carved the canyon<br>
that sealed Traica, Tenrou manages to wiggle out of her grip, but
not for long. </p>

<p>&quot;Do you have to keep hugging me?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Whats wrong don't you like having a pretty girl holding
you?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;No..well...I mean.yes..but..&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You are afraid of becoming your father.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;!?! How did you know that?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Easy silly. I have naturally good sense of perception. I
wasn't worshiped for hundreds of<br>
years just because I am pretty...Not that I wouldn't be
surprised, have you seen the Iksar<br>
and Sarnak women? Yuck!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Am I really that transparent?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;No. My blessing of insight allows me to see your
suffering Tenrou.Your heart aches from<br>
being shunned by nearly everyone you meet, including your own
father. As you make your<br>
journeys, you feel your chances of enjoying peace slipping away.
You burn with intense<br>
hatred and rage for your father, yet at the same time you quake
at the very thought of<br>
him.&quot; </p>

<p>Tenrou broke away from her embrace and began to walk away,
trembling violent. &quot;Shut<br>
up! I...am afraid of ... no one. I ....am not afraid.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Then why haven't you stood up to him? Why at every
chance do you back down? Why<br>
do you forsake your promise to your mother?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Be..cause....I... am&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;afraid.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;..leave me alone.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Tenrou-&quot; She gently took hold of his hand, trying
to ease his trembling. &quot;You are a gentle<br>
passionate, caring person, and that is what you fear most. You
are just like your father.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I am nothing like him!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You are just like him and you know it. No else could,
seduce their greatest enemy and<br>
bravely stare down the critics of the love that had formed. And
like just like him, you have<br>
lost sight of your way.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;...&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You know what you must do.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;But-&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;No buts! Come on lets go!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Wait!! What are you doing!?! NO! NO! NO! Thats a long
fa- AAAAAAAAAAAAH!!&quot; </p>

<p>The massive true form of Triaca. The green dragon of myth and
legend sailed through the<br>
canyon, cruising just over the river, and with one flap of her
immense wings, she leapt into<br>
the heavens.<br>
------------------------------- </p>

<p><br>
&quot;Damn you Raziel!! Why do you continue to toy with
them?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot; It is always more satisfactory to savor the
moment.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Because of your incessant 'savoring', they have freed
those 2 traitorous dragons! And<br>
now they make their way to have the loyal remaining ones rebel
against me!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You and I both now they are not loyal, servitude that is
won by conquest is never willing<br>
nor loyal.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;And what does it matter! I can not afford to have the
Ring of Scale turn against me! Not<br>
now that I am so close to removing the others grasps from
Norrath! I will not lose this<br>
because of some stupid fabrication of a being that hasn't been
alive in a eternity!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;And what do you need them for Ka'ruya? You beat them all
before by yourself. Now you<br>
have an army to support you and you have me.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Yes..You are right. Raziel, I could not have come so far
without you. I am glad that you<br>
are mine.&quot; </p>

<p>She smiled as Raziel took her into his arms. </p>

