every-what the!&quot; </p>

<p>The door fell of its hinges and tumbled backwards, crashing to
the ground, Tenrou now<br>
laying ontop of the door. </p>

<p>&quot;This is becoming a habit Tenrou.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Don't I know it....ow.....my back....&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Your so great Tennie!&quot; Traica squealed as she
helped him to his feet, snuggling up<br>
against him when he was righted. </p>

<p>&quot;Tennie?&quot; Both Reyas and Leylia exclaimed </p>

<p>&quot;What? I can't have a pet name for my love and my
lover?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;!!!!Tenrou! You did what with my sister!!!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Well..I uh..Hey look at these cool paintings!&quot;<br>
---------------------------------- </p>

<p>It was am uneasy ride up, Reyas was constantly looking for a
chance to hurt Tenrou, but<br>
couldn't because he was being shielded by Traica who did not want
to let go of him. But<br>
the situation quickly ended, when the elevator reached the top
and they were greeted by<br>
the vast atrium, that Reyas and Traica&#146;s home, the home of
the Ring of Scale. </p>

<p>&quot;This is home?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Yeah! Ain't it grand!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;And I thought Felwithe with elaborate!&quot; </p>

<p>They all vacated the elevator and wandered around looking at
the various plants,<br>
eventually coming to a empty section. The sound of small beating
wings coming from<br>
behind became apparent and as they turned they came face to face
with a flying pink cat. </p>

<p>The winged cat fluttered around the group, eventually hovering
upside down in front of<br>
Reyas. </p>

<p>&quot;Still as poofy as ever Silverwing&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;!!!! WHY YOU!!!!!!! You haven't changed Reyas! grrrr...I
am not poofy! I am pleasantly<br>
furred! Now I know where that erudite got that from.....Well any
way. It's bit a long time<br>
big bro!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Yeah.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Silvie!&quot; Traica cheered and snatched Silverwing out
of the air bouncing her around. </p>

<p>&quot; Hi-Tr-Ai-ca! St--op th-at------- di-zz-y!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Sorry&quot; She cooed letting the dizzy dragon, and
wound up with Silverwing sitting ontop<br>
of Traica's head. </p>

<p>&quot;HEY!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Tough&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Silverwing get of her head!&quot; A new voice spoke from
behind them. </p>

<p>&quot;Ahhh..You are no fun Phara...&quot; </p>

<p>Her weight was lifted from Traica's head and she fluttered
over to the voice, landing on<br>
the shoulder of an exception to his jet-black hair, the mirror
image of Reyas. </p>

<p>&quot;How were things down in the underworld bro?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Hot.&quot; </p>

<p>Leylia's head shifted back and forth between Reyas and Phara
Dar, amazed by their<br>
likeness. </p>

<p>&quot;You two are-&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Twins&quot;<br>
&quot;Twins&quot; They answered at the same time. </p>

<p>&quot;AAH! I hate it when you do that! ME!?! STOP THAT!!&quot;<br>
&quot;AAH! I hate it when you do that! ME!?! STOP THAT!!&quot; </p>

<p>Traica leaned against Leylia and whispered into her ear
&quot;They are always doing that. If<br>
you think it's annoying now, try putting up with it for several
millennia...sigh. But<br>
forgetting the difference in hair color, they have nothing in
common after the physical<br>
appearance. Like night and day. Phara doesn't like anything from
Norrath unlike Reyas.<br>
Phara is also several times stronger then Reyas.... supposedly,
I've always had the<br>
suspicion that Reyas holds back...;Which is why Reyas was the one
who got cast out and<br>
not Phara. No one but me and Reyas ever disagrees with him.&quot;
</p>

<p>&quot;I see you have brought some friends with you brother.
You still have so much love for<br>
them even after all this time as one of Cazic's servants?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Yes. Nothing could change that, by the way how do you
keep your lips from chapping?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;What?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You obviously most see Veeshan allot, I was just wonder
how you keep your lips from<br>
chapping after all that b-&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You really haven't changed a bit!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Why do you continue to fight against Veeshan?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;She betrayed us and the planes! She corrupted the others
with her lies! She destroyed the<br>
teachings of the Nameless, she is making us forget about the word
of the void!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Oh please! Don't tell me you still believe in the that
rubbish! You are going to put all your<br>
faith in something that doesn't exist.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Whether it exists or not is something you must believe
for yourself. But from here you<br>
must have seen what she has done to Norrath! It is in pain! She
has resurrected everything<br>
that is wrong, she is killing that plane!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;So what! Let it die for all I care! Our life is good
here, so why would we want to disrupt<br>
it? And even if we did why would we want to be ruled by
mortals?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;!?!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You think I am stupid? I know that old myth, the
dragoons, the masters of dragons! No<br>
one is going to rule me or any of us!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;What do you think Veeshan is doing!!!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Shut up!&quot; his first slammed into Reyas's stomach
removing all the air from his lungs, and<br>
the palm of his other hand smashed into Reyas's head, causing
Reyas to fly across the<br>
room and bounce off a pillar and lay motionless. </p>

<p>&quot;Reyas!&quot;<br>
&quot;Reyas!&quot;<br>
&quot;Rey-Rey!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Now. All of you get out and do not come back!&quot; </p>

<p>Leylia stepped in front of Phara. </p>

<p>&quot;We aren't leaving, with out your help. We need you to
liberate Norrath from Veeshan!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;In case you weren't listening, we happen to like
Veeshan, and I could care less what<br>
happens to Norrath.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Phara. I can look into your eyes and see that you don't
truly like Veeshan. She used your<br>
code against you, and rules with an iron hand. Please join us,
rise up against her.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Why should I? I am not going to be ruled, not any one,
and especially not a mortal like<br>
you!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I don't want to rule you! Join us as friends,
equals.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;LIES! All Lies! You lie like the mortal you are! I have
had enough of your clucking<br>
tongue! DIE!&quot; His fist shot out aimed for her head, but met
only air as she vanished. Phara<br>
wheeled around 180 degrees to come face to face with her in her
dazzling gray armor<br>
wielding the two halves of the Masamune. </p>

<p>Phara glared at her, burning with rage outstretched his hand
and a huge broadsword made<br>
of mana materialized. A burst of light illuminated his back
briefly, and glancing over his<br>
shoulder, Tenrou was covered in dazzling gray chainmail, wielding
the Kusanagi. </p>

<p>&quot;Xygoz!&quot; </p>

<p>A incredibly large, burly Human appeared in front of Tenrou,
whirling a mana scythe<br>
above his head. The four locked their eyes upon each other,
tension building, waiting on<br>
someone to make the first move. Xygoz made it. </p>

<p>&quot;Let's go bub!&quot; His scythe cut the air, just missing
Tenrou as he ducked thrusting the<br>
Kusanagi upwards. Phara swung at Leylia's midsection, just
stopped by her the sword in<br>
her left hand, her right sword stabbed at his head missing as he
bobbed away. </p>

<p>Xygoz's scythe sliced air again and again. Tenrou backflipped
away, Xygoz gathering<br>
mana </p>

<p>&quot;BEZERKER'S RAGE!&quot; He made a cut toward Tenrou, a
second scythe leapt out of the<br>
original, spinning through the air, circling Tenrou, spinning
around him faster and faster,<br>
turning into some kind of mana barrier, suspending him in mid
air. Xygoz charged forward<br>
and leapt toward Tenrou, scythe ready to taste blood.<br>
------------------------------------------------------<br>
Leylia's blades blocked Phara's swings again and again. Sparks
showered from each blow. </p>

<p>&quot;INFINISLASH!&quot; </p>

<p>Phara doubled, then tripled, then quadrip-led, each swinging
at Leylia faster then could be<br>
seen, each swing chipping away at her defense, each one bringing
her closer to death.<br>
--------------------------------------------------- </p>

<p>The scythe closed in and cut through the barrier, and nothing
more. Tenrou reappearing<br>
behind Xygoz. </p>

<p>&quot;BLOODY SLICE!&quot; The red crescent wave engulfed Xygoz
and slammed into the<br>
ground, in one bounce, his scythe shattered and on the second, he
lost his form, and on the<br>
final, he lay still in infant form, purring softly.<br>
--------------------------------------------------- </p>

<p>The multiple broadswords missed again and again, and slowly
one by one each form<br>
winked away as Leylia cut through them, leaving only the true
Phara Dar. He roared in<br>
hatred at her and charge, with one swift movement, one blade head
his broadsword away<br>
and the other smashed into nothing. A small sphere of mana formed
in her hands and<br>
slammed into Phara's gut lifting him into the air, and crushed
him against a pillar. His form<br>
gave way to his infant shape as he fell down face first.. </p>

<p>A hand on her shoulder startled Leylia, turning slightly
toward it, she breathed s igh of<br>
relief top see it was Reyas, though he was slightly bruised. </p>

<p>Pushing himself to all fours Phara's shape shimmered and
restored itself to the black haired<br>
mirror of Reyas. Still sore, he sat against the battered pillar. </p>

<p>&quot;No! Non ancora. Sono il pi forte dei draghi, io non
presenter a qualunque! Non!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;What did he say?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;No! Not again. I am the strongest of the dragons, I
won't submit to any one! I won't!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Phara. Neither I nor Tenrou, wants to rule you. We want
to be allies, friends. We want to<br>
do this of out own will, not because someone forced us. If we
don't stand up Veeshan,<br>
then everyone wiill suffer, mortals, dragons, and gods
alike.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;How ca....n I trust you...I have heard this
before...long .....ago...&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Because&quot; She took one of her swords and placed it
in his hand, leaning her chest against<br>
the sharp tip. &quot;You can. I trust you, no matter how much you
have been hurt, no matter<br>
how much you dislike those not like you, you do wish to be free,
just like us. So take this<br>
chance, join us please..if not then kill me so that I may die
free.&quot; </p>

<p>Phara smiled weakly. &quot;You get all the luck bro...Such
honor and beauty in one package.<br>
How rare...I almost..forgot what it was like..all those years
ago...&quot; He turned to the<br>
others, who were huddled together, taking care of Xygoz. </p>

<p>&quot;What do you say guys? Hang with the mortals, kick
Veeshans butt?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Most definitly!&quot;<br>
&quot;Wouldn&#146;t have it any other way!&quot;<br>
&quot;Aye!&quot;<br>
&quot;I'm in!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Then it is settled. We go to the sky plane, Veeshan had
better watch out!&quot; </p>

<p>The newly reunited Ring of Scale dragons cheered for a moment,
but they were<br>
interrupted. </p>

<p>Laughter and the sound of metal gauntlets clapping filled the
air, the weary combatants<br>
turned their gaze up, to lay their sight upon a man wearing a
silver mask appluading,<br>
hovering above them. </p>

<p>(*Music Cue: Duel of the Fates-Star Wars The Phantom Menace) </p>

<p>&quot;Impressive. Truly impressive! You really are the masters
of the dragons, the Dragoons of<br>
lore.&quot; </p>

<p>Silver Mask cast his gaze upon Leylia &quot;But I would expect
no less from one sired of my<br>
loins, even if sullied by an elven wench.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;What!?!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Silver Mask roared with laughter. &quot;You never cease
to amaze me Reyas, of one so old,<br>
you would have developed a little spine to tell her the truth. To
tell her who she is.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Reyas what is he talking about?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I..uh..Silver Mask..o..&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Tell me Reyas!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;...&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Since he is lost for word I shall tell you, I am the one
who gave you life girl. Without me<br>
you would not be here!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;What are you talking about! Raziel is
my....no..you're..you can't be...&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Raziel&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Dad.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I'm sorry Leylia..I just didn't know how to tell
you.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;I dont; understand! Why would you join Veeshan! She
killed mother!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;It was inevitable. A toy always loses it's desirabiliy
after time, it was just your mother's<br>
time.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;YOU LIE!!!!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Do I really?&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You loved her! You had to!!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Why would I have had to love her? Because she was not an
erudite, because she was a<br>
Grail Knight? It just made the conquest more interesting.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;SHUT UP! YOU'RE NOT MY FATHER!&quot; </p>

<p>Raziel disappeared and reappeared on the floor several feet in
front her. </p>

<p>&quot;Believe what you want. But heed my words girl, do no
attempt to enter the Sky Plane.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;And why not! Are you scared off us! Scared that we will
rise against you and win! Scared<br>
that we will bring about the Twilight!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;HA!!&quot; Raziel's laughter grew even laughter.
&quot;All this time, and even know you don't even<br>
know what it is. You have come so far, killed so many,, all for a
myth you don't even<br>
understand.&quot; </p>

<p><br>
&quot;I........&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Stupid child.&quot; Raziel turned to the battered Phara
Dar. &quot;I suggest if you wish to stay of<br>
use to Veeshan, that you kill her and her friends.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;No..I will not be under her heel anymore&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;You try my patience Phara Dar.&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Good!&quot; Phara painfully stood up and reformed his
sword. &quot;Cause I am about to give you<br>
the beating of your miserable mortal life!&quot; </p>

<p>&quot;Is that so?&quot; Raziel raised his hand towards Phara,
and immediately Phara clawed madly at<br>
an unseen hand crushing his throat. The hand lifted him up, the
grip becoming tighter, until<br>
the hand threw him away, careening into the other four, knocking
him unconscious. </p>

<p>&quot;PHARA!&quot; </p>

<p>All the dragons minus Phara, instantly shifted filling the
atrium as they swelled to their<br>
enormous size. </p>

<p>&quot;Such tempers&quot; Raziel outstretched his hands each
one pointing at the nearest dragon. He<br>
then slammed his hands together, causing Reyas and Silverwing to
buttheads. They passed<br>
out, turning back into infants. At that moment four beams cut
toward Raziel, they didn't even touch as they bent away and
collided with the walls. Miming several actions, the remaining
members of the Ring of Scale found them selves being tossed, strangled and pulverized by thin air. In only a few moments, the only ones remaining standing were Raziel, Tenrou and Leylia, the dragons lay unconscious purring in their infant shape, strewn every where across the atrium. </p>

<p>Raziel turned away his back to Leylia. With no actions or spells, an azure blue gate opened. Large floating islands hovered in the distance. </p>

<p>&quot;Why send 5 dragons to an erudite&#146;s job.&quot; </p>

<p>Looking over his shoulder he spoke once more. &quot;Heed my words Leylia, or this shall happen to you.&quot; He stepped forward into the gate, it rippled like water for a few moments<br>
from where he entered.<br>
---------------------------<br>
End of This Chapter<br>
-------------------------- </p>

<p><br>
-----------------------------<br>
Preview of Next Chapter!<br>
------------------------------ </p>

<p>The final battle is at hand, and in an unbelievable display of power. Raziel has placed deep doubts within the mind of Leylia and Tenrou. If he can single handily beat all 7 members of the Ring of Scale without effort, what would Veeshan be like, and as if that wasn't even could they really take on both of them? But even with such bleak odds, their own abilities can not be underestimated. So place your bets folks cause this fight could go either way, the only dead cert is that some one is going to die. Will Veeshan succeed in her domination of the alter planes, will the dragoons conquer? Find out in the next exciting chapter: Terminal Battle; The Death of - </p>
</body>
